fields.name: Bunny Senpai
fields.desc:
#### Description
There exists $200000$ tiles, numbered from $1$ to $200000$, and a bunny, initially at tile $1$. From tile $i$, the bunny can jump $x$ tiles forward if and only if $\gcd(i, x) = 1$ (i.e. the bunny will end up at tile $i + x$ after the jump).

You will need to answer $T$ independent test cases. For the $j$-th case, find the number of ways to reach tile $N_j$ from tile $1$. Output all the answers modulo a prime number $M$.
#### Constraints - $1 \le T \le 2 \times 10^5$ - $4 \times 10^8 \le M \le 10^9 + 10$ - $M$ is a prime number. - $1 \le N_j \le 2 \times 10^5$
####Input ``` T M N[1] N[2] ... N[T] ```
####Output Output $T$ lines, each consisting of the number of ways modulo $M$.
#### Sample Input ``` 3 1000000007 5 1 100 ```
#### Sample Output ``` 7 1 592090280 ```
#### Explanation All the possible ways for $N = 5$ are: - $1 - 2 - 3 - 4 - 5$ - $1 - 2 - 3 - 5$ - $1 - 2 - 5$ - $1 - 3 - 4 - 5$ - $1 - 3 - 5$ - $1 - 4 - 5$ - $1 - 5$

fields.name: How to Create a Discord Bot using Python
fields.desc:
In order to work with the Python library and the Discord API, we must first create a Discord Bot account.
Here are the steps to creating a Discord Bot account. 1. Make sure you're logged on to the [Discord website](https://discord.com). 2. Navigate to the [application page](https://discord.com/developers/applications). 3. Click on the 'New Application' button. 4. Give the application a name and click Create 5. Go to the 'Bot' tab and then click Add Bot You will have to confirm by clicking "Yes, do it!" Keep the default settings for Public Bot (checked) and Require OAuth2 Code Grant (unchecked).

Your bot has been created. The next step is to copy the token. This token is your bot's password so don't share it with anybody. It could allow someone to log in to your bot and do all sorts of bad things.

You can regenerate the token if it accidentally gets shared.
For the remaining part of the tutorial, please refer to this [blog post](https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/create-a-discord-bot-with-python/). Credits: [Beau Carnes](https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/author/beau/)
